<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-05-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-05-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="642" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d642">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.001 Au 4/5.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-05-03">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 3, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>President Tancréde Auguste died on the 2d instant. Congress will convene
                            today to elect his successor.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Furniss</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>